<h2>Stress tests</h2>

<div class="card">
  <h3 style="margin:6px 0;">HighConcurrencyJob (concurrency only, max=100, sleep=0.1s)</h3>
  <%= form_with url: enqueue_many_path(job: "high_concurrency"), method: :post, local: true do %>
    <label>bucket</label> <input name="attrs[bucket]" value="hot"><br>
    <label>max</label>    <input name="attrs[max]"    value="100" size="6"><br>
    <label>count</label>  <input name="count"         value="500" size="6"><br>
    <button>Flood with HighConcurrencyJob</button>
  <% end %>
  <p style="font-size:12px;color:#6b7280;">Watch <code>/dispatch_policy</code> dashboard: <code>in_flight</code> should rise toward <code>max</code>; <code>avg tick</code> should stay low.</p>
</div>

<div class="card">
  <h3 style="margin:6px 0;">HighThrottleJob (throttle only, rate=10k/min, sleep=0.05s)</h3>
  <%= form_with url: enqueue_many_path(job: "high_throttle"), method: :post, local: true do %>
    <label>endpoint</label> <input name="attrs[endpoint]" value="hot"><br>
    <label>rate</label>     <input name="attrs[rate]"     value="10000" size="8"><br>
    <label>count</label>    <input name="count"           value="2000"  size="6"><br>
    <button>Flood with HighThrottleJob</button>
  <% end %>
  <p style="font-size:12px;color:#6b7280;">Bucket fills instantly so the limiter is your worker pool: tick should saturate <code>admission_batch_size</code> per partition.</p>
</div>

<h2>Fairness intra-tick</h2>

<div class="card">
  <h3 style="margin:6px 0;">FairnessDemoJob (5 tenants, uneven backlog)</h3>
  <%= form_with url: fairness_demo_flood_path, method: :post, local: true do %>
    <label>hot tenant count</label> <input name="hot_count"  value="500" size="6"><br>
    <label>cold tenant count (×4)</label> <input name="cold_count" value="10"  size="6"><br>
    <button>Flood the unfair workload</button>
  <% end %>
  <p style="font-size:12px;color:#6b7280;">
    Enqueues <code>hot_count</code> jobs for tenant <code>hot</code> and
    <code>cold_count</code> each for tenants <code>cold-1..cold-4</code>.
    The policy declares <code>tick_admission_budget&nbsp;30</code> and
    <code>fairness half_life:&nbsp;30.seconds</code>, so each tick admits
    ~6 jobs per tenant; cold drain in 1-2 ticks while hot progresses at
    the capped rate. Watch
    <code>/dispatch_policy/policies/fairness_demo</code> — the
    <strong>decayed_admits</strong> column on each partition is the EWMA
    used to order them inside the tick.
  </p>
</div>

<h2>Adaptive concurrency (self-tuning cap)</h2>

<div class="card">
  <h3 style="margin:6px 0;">AdaptiveDemoJob (initial_max=3, target_lag_ms=500)</h3>
  <%= form_with url: enqueue_many_path(job: "adaptive_demo"), method: :post, local: true do %>
    <label>tenant</label> <input name="attrs[tenant]" value="acme"><br>
    <label>count</label>  <input name="count" value="50" size="6"><br>
    <button>Flood AdaptiveDemoJob</button>
  <% end %>
  <p style="font-size:12px;color:#6b7280;">
    Cap starts at 3 per tenant. Each perform sleeps ~300ms; a burst
    of 50 will queue up at the adapter, the EWMA queue lag will
    cross 500ms, and <code>current_max</code> shrinks via 0.95×
    per observation. A quiet period of 30s lets the cap grow back
    +1 per fast success. State lives in
    <code>dispatch_policy_adaptive_concurrency_stats</code> — query
    it directly to watch the AIMD react in real time.
  </p>
</div>

<h2>Sharding (shard_by)</h2>

<div class="card">
  <h3 style="margin:6px 0;">ShardedJob (account_id → 4 shards, queue = shard)</h3>
  <%= form_with url: enqueue_many_path(job: "sharded"), method: :post, local: true do %>
    <label>account_id</label> <input name="attrs[account_id]" value="acct-A"><br>
    <label>max</label>        <input name="attrs[max]"        value="5"  size="6"><br>
    <label>count</label>      <input name="count"             value="80" size="6"><br>
    <button>Flood with ShardedJob</button>
  <% end %>
  <p style="font-size:12px;color:#6b7280;">
    The job routes itself to <code>shard-N</code> (queue = shard). Launch
    <code>4.times { |i| DispatchTickLoopJob.perform_later("sharded", "shard-#{i}") }</code>
    in <code>bin/rails console</code> to enable parallel admission across shards.
    Watch <code>/dispatch_policy/partitions?policy=sharded</code> with the shard filter.
  </p>
</div>

